Temiloluwa O’Peters Julius Berger has said it closed the 2019 financial year with great success, achieving an increase in turnover of 37 per cent. The Managing Director, Dr Lars Richter, said this at the firm’s virtual 2020 Annual General Meeting. The AGM was also the celebration of the company’s 50th anniversary since its it was registered as a Nigerian company. Richter said the company ended 2019 on a very high note with a high cash flow and increase in profitability. He hinged the success on “powerful operational performance”, saying the company increasingly modernised its human resource structures and systems, invested in new equipment and sort to identify and explore opportunities for diversification of its business. Commenting on the ongoing projects of the company, Ritcher said the firm was working day and night to ensure timely project completion of the Abuja-Kaduna-Zaria-Kano Road, the Lagos-Shagamu Expressway and the Bodo-Bonny Road. Ritcher anchored the company’s future on strengthening core construction business, client mix and the group’s subsidiaries as well as diversification with a greater balance of private sector projects. He added that focus would remain on successfully executing projects of national priority in the public sector. The company paid out a dividend of two naira for every share of 50kobo held as well as a bonus share to shareholders for the business year ended December 31, 2019. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com